Description: Lower wall sherd with turn of flaring foot of East Greek (?) pottery cup; glazed inside and out; reserved underside; inscriptions cut on exterior of wall and on underside.
Curator's comments: This might be high quality East Greek.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 530)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.741)
